      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Detail of outcome</h2>

      <div class="consultation-outcome-detail">
        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<h2 id="proposed-revision-of-existing-fees-for-statutory-services">Proposed revision of existing fees for statutory services</h2>

<p>350 organisations were directly contacted by email or letter to alert them to the first consultation.</p>

<p>We received 20 responses to this consultation; 13 consultation questionnaire responses and 7 by email or letter.</p>

<p>The published report summarises the responses made by respondents either through completed questionnaires or by separate email or letter correspondence.</p>

<h2 id="proposed-introduction-of--fees-for-statutory-services">Proposed introduction of  fees for statutory services</h2>

<p>370 organisations were contacted by email to alert them to the second consultation.</p>

<p>We received 61 responses to this consultation; 51 consultation questionnaire responses and 10 by email or letter.</p>

<p>The published report summarises the responses made by respondents either through completed questionnaires or by separate email or letter correspondence.</p>
</div>
</div>

      </div>



      <section class="original-consultation">
        <header>
          <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  " id="original-consultation-title">Original consultation</h2>

        </header>


    <section class="app-c-banner app-c-banner--grid" aria-label="Notice">
      <h2 class="app-c-banner__title">Summary</h2>
  <p class="app-c-banner__desc">
          Seeking views on proposed changes to charges for some APHA statutory and certification services.
        <br></br><br></br>
        <strong>This consultation was held on <a href="https://consult.defra.gov.uk/">another website</a>.</strong>

  </p>

    <p class="app-c-banner__desc">        This consultation ran from<br></br><span class="consultation-date"><time datetime="2015-10-26T00:00:00.000+00:00">26 October 2015</time> to
        <time datetime="2015-12-15T00:00:00.000+00:00">11:59pm on 14 December 2015</time></span>
</p>
</section>


      </section>


    <div class="consultation-description">
      <h2 class="gem-c-heading  gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Consultation description</h2>

      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency (<abbr title="Animal and Plant Health Agency">APHA</abbr>) is seeking views on proposed changes to charges for some of the services we provide for the protection of animal health and welfare, and the introduction of charges for some other services.</p>

<p>The changes will apply to <abbr title="Animal and Plant Health Agency">APHA</abbr> services provided across Great Britain.</p>

<p>There are two online consultations at <a rel="external" href="https://consult.defra.gov.uk/">https://consult.defra.gov.uk/</a>:</p>

<p>The first consultation is about changing existing charges for the following services:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Poultry Health Scheme</li>
  <li>Salmonella National Control Programme</li>
  <li>Border Inspection Posts</li>
  <li>approval of bovine and porcine semen collection centres and artificial breeding</li>
</ul>

<p><a rel="external" href="https://consult.defra.gov.uk/apha/apha-seeks-views-on-revised-fees-for-statutory-se">Find out more about this consultation</a></p>

<p>The second consultation is about introducing new charges for the following services:</p>

<ul>
  <li>approval and registration of animal by-products sites</li>
  <li>approval of animal gatherings</li>
  <li>administration of pet passports</li>
</ul>

<p><a rel="external" href="https://consult.defra.gov.uk/apha/apha-seeks-views-on-new-fees-for-statutory-servic">Find out more about this consultation</a></p>

<p>The aim of the proposal changes is to reduce taxpayer subsidy of <abbr title="Animal and Plant Health Agency">APHA</abbr> services by transferring some of the costs to those who benefit from the agencyâ€™s services.</p>

<p>Additional information and details of meetings held with stakeholders about these proposals is available on the archived <a rel="external" href="http://webarchive.nationalarchives.gov.uk/20140707135733/http://www.defra.gov.uk/ahvla-en/tests-and-services/charges-for-ahvla-services/">AHVLA web pages</a></p>

</div>
</div>


    </div>


